  "title": "Dental Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>- To assist dentists in carrying out treatments.</p><p>- Ensure patients' comfort during treatment.</p><p>- Prepare treatment room by stocking dental materials and ensuring equipment are maintained and in tip-top condition.</p><p>- Sterilization of instruments and maintenance of clinic cleanliness and hygiene standards.</p><p>- Assist in adhoc duties that may be assigned by the Supervisor.</p><p>- Manage appointments and provide customer service to patients.</p><p>- Attend to queries from call-in patients.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>- Candidates must possess at least Primary/Secondary School/\"N Level\"/\"O Level\", Professional Certificate, Nitec in any field or equivalent.</p><p>- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.</p><p>- Good team player who is mature, organised, reliable, responsible, takes initiative and able to work independently with minimum supervision.</p><p>- Willingness to travel to other clinic when needed (transport reimbursable).</p><p>- Dental Assistants with relevant dental experience will be compensated accordingly.</p><p>- Able to work evenings until 9pm (Shift work during clinic operating hours).</p><p>- IT literate.</p>",
